{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2ca5d0be-1e98-4ba1-8aa1-97609e29bfcf","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `.csproj`**\n```xml\n<!-- Change -->\n<TargetFramework>net10.0</TargetFramework>\n<!-- To -->\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`**\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`**\n```dockerfile\n# Replace all image tags\nmcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0\nmcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0\n```\n\nAfter updating, run `dotnet restore && dotnet build` to verify everything compiles. Also update any NuGet packages (e.g. `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*`, `Microsoft.Extensions.*`) to their 11.x versions.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d66e8068-cb0d-4341-96b6-d7f7a4724c35","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward informational question — I don't need to explore any codebase since they're describing their setup. Let me provide concise guidance.","outputTokens":281},"id":"f7ff0ceb-5fab-4db8-88a7-eea311e8cf01","timestamp":"2026-04-08T01:02:50.667Z","parentId":"9ae8ce0c-d36e-4719-96c9-c53259be8ee0"}
